President Joseph R. Biden Jr. has authorized the Secretary of Defense and the Secretary of Homeland Security to order members and units of the Selected Reserve and Individual Ready Reserve of the Coast Guard to active duty without their consent. This authorization is in accordance with section 12304(f) of title 10, United States Code, and is applicable when the Coast Guard is not operating as a service in the Department of the Navy. The mobilizations under this authorization are limited to a maximum of 3,000 total members at any one time, with no more than 450 members from the Individual Ready Reserve. These Reserve Component forces will be deployed to augment the active forces for Operation Atlantic Resolve, enhancing the United States' ability to sustain its heightened level of presence and operations in support of United States European Command. The Executive Order issued by President Biden can be found enclosed. The date of the announcement was July 13, 2023.